definitions.definition: Of or related to Cyrenaicism , the philosophical school founded by Aristippus of Cyrene and codified by Aristippus the Younger .
Synonym of Cyrenian , of or related to Cyrene .
Synonym of Cyrenaican , of or related to Cyrenaica , the area around Cyrene in northeastern Libya .
